The paper deals with the study of infinite games, which is a topic that falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of coinduction and backward coinduction also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also involves the analysis of strategies and equilibria, which is a common theme in the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the study of rational behavior in games can also be related to the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
